        "tagName": "p",
        "properties": {},
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "If you're developing software using the NodeJS runtime environment you're probably aware that you might want have multiple projects using different node versions, say one using 10 and another 12. This could be due to a number of reasons. It gets annoying switching between node versions manually.",
